**Solution:**
Add the following lines to the `%files` section of `gawk.spec` to claim all unpackaged artifacts. Use wildcards for predictable paths like plugins and docs, and explicit macros for system paths:

```spec
/usr/bin/gawkbug
%{_sysconfdir}/profile.d/gawk.sh
%{_sysconfdir}/profile.d/gawk.csh
%{_includedir}/gawkapi.h
%{_libdir}/debug/%{?buildarch:*/}%{name}/*
%{_libdir}/gawk/*.so
/usr/share/info/gawk_*.png
/usr/share/man/man3/*.gz
```

Insert these lines anywhere within the existing `%files` block. They claim the missing binaries, headers, shell profile hooks, split debuginfo files, dynamically loaded awk modules, and auxiliary documentation without altering existing packaging logic. Save and rebuild.
